3. Recognizes that security of United Nations personnel is essential for UNAMI to carry out its work and calls upon the Government of Iraq and other Member States to provide security and logistical support;

4. Welcomes contributions of Member States in providing UNAMI with necessary resources and support, and calls upon Member States to continue to provide sufficient resources;

5. Expresses its intention to review the mandate of UNAMI in twelve months or sooner, if requested by the Government of Iraq;

